    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="410"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C111/890a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Diplomatic Officers in the American Republics</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-01">October 1,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sirs</hi>: There is enclosed herewith a copy of the message
                    which, under date of September 27, 1935, I sent to the Chairman of the Second
                        <pb facs="0628" n="526" xml:id="pg_526"/> Committee of the League Assembly
                    regarding the economic program adopted by that Committee.</p>
                <p>I desire you to furnish a copy of this message to the Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs; in your covering note, you will please inform the Minister that I am
                    sure that he also will welcome the program adopted by the Committee as evidence
                    of the growing worldwide support for the fundamental principles embodied in the
                    agreements worked out at the Montevideo Conference.<note n="6" xml:id="d410fn6"
                        >For correspondence concerning this Conference, see <ref
                            target="frus1933v04#pg_1">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1933, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, pp. 1</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
